description.title: Tableau Dashboard Developer / Analyst
description: Professional, Prince 2 Qualified, Data Senior Business Analyst with a successful track record in health data services environments. Keen and experienced Tableau user, with excellent analysis, IT liter…

bio:
After 13 years data experience within the NHS, I set up DG Data Services Ltd. This is a data analysis consultancy business using Tableau and other data visualization tools. My clients range from US Healthcare, Content Marketing, Internet Service Providers, Legal Firms, UK Digital Marketing, to name a few. I build dashboards and undertake data analysis to clients requirements and advise where appropriate. 

I also set up the North West England Tableau User Group. Bringing people together across different sectors to learn and share best practice in using Tableau.

I have developed a suite of analysis reports using Tableau in use across various industries and ensuring the detail is easy to comprehend. I have an excellent understanding of many different data sets, related systems and data warehouses including intermediate knowledge SQL.

I have also developed IT and analysis skills of many professionals of different levels ensuring they understand their data in language they and their audience can comprehend.

Specialities:  Data Analysis, Excel, Tableau, Health Data Sets (UK and US), Cancer data, Health IT Systems, T-SQL, Internet Usage Data, Legal Data, Electronic Patient Records, System Configuration, Data Migration, IT Training, Project Management.
